18/01/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government announced on Tuesday (17 January) that it is launching a reform of the healthcare sector to bring it in line with EU standards.
Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu said the overhaul would uproot pervasive corruption and boost efficiency.
In other news Tuesday, a second member of the main opposition Social Democratic Party (PSD), Dan Ioan Popescu, resigned amid corruption allegations.
PSD executive president Adrian Nastase stepped down earlier in the week.
(Nine o'clock - 18/01/06;
Reuters - 17/01/06)
